The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                      
	 East Bengal defeated SAI, NSEC 4-2 in the ONGC Bengal Premier League on Saturday. East Bengals Aman Balgu who won both his singles and doubles matches was declared the player of the match.          
	 Satya Roy, coach of former athlete and Asian Games gold medallist Jyotirmoyee Sikdar, is in critical condition. Roy, 68 had been admitted to the Rabindranath Tagore Research Centre in Behrampore after a heart attack last week.                 
	 The CAB grounds committee on Saturday decided on the expansion of three grounds  Rangers, YMCA and the Town Club  so that Twenty20 cricket could be hosted there. Twenty20 cricket requires a big ground and so we are looking to extend the boundaries of these grounds so that more and more Twenty20 matches can be played there. We will try to shift the practice pitches elsewhere so that the long off boundaries can be stretched, a CAB official said.                
